## The Revised Thesis: Three Sequential Waves of the Same Crisis

The key insight from all the research is this: we are not looking at a single credit event. We are looking at a **three-wave contagion that has specific, mechanical sequencing** — and only Wave 1 has partially played out. Waves 2 and 3 are unpriced.

> *Wave 1 [Underway]: BDC/alt-manager liquidity stress — partially priced*
> *Wave 2 [Starting]: Insurance solvency erosion — not priced*
> *Wave 3 [Forward]: Sovereign term premium + dollar debasement — partially priced, wrong instruments*

